    <item>
      <title>Scene I — The Invitation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Invitation&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Desire does not knock. It waits to be noticed.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Larissa had not meant to linger on the photograph.&#xD;&#xA;Yet something in the woman’s eyes—faded, knowing, almost amused—&#xD;&#xA;refused to release her.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;The letter arrived the same evening.&#xD;&#xA;No return address. No explanation.&#xD;&#xA;Only her name, written as though someone had practiced it&#xD;&#xA;for years.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;She should not have opened it.&#xD;&#xA;But longing is a quiet persuader.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-6/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-2/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scene II — The Edge</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Edge&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Fear is only the body remembering its limits.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Vanessa stood at the glass balcony, twenty stories above certainty.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;The woman beside her smiled—not kindly, not cruelly—&#xD;&#xA;but knowingly.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;“Jump,” she said softly. “Or live the same life forever.”&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Vanessa realized then—&#xD;&#xA;some offers are not meant to be survived.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-1/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-3/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scene III — The Crossing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-3/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-3/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Crossing&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Love becomes dangerous when it chooses a side.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Anika knew the moment she should have turned back.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;But his voice—calm, certain, inevitable—&#xD;&#xA;felt like destiny wearing a uniform.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;War was not coming.&#xD;&#xA;It had already chosen her.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-2/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-4/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scene IV — The Hunger</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-4/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Hunger&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Kindness can be a disguise for appetite.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;The doctor’s home was warm.&#xD;&#xA;Too warm.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Sabrina noticed how the doors locked softly behind her.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;How generosity always came with a condition—&#xD;&#xA;unspoken, but deeply understood.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Some shelters are designed to keep you in.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-3/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-5/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scene V — The Choice</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-5/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-5/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Choice&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Desire multiplies when it is divided.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Mylakena had never imagined wanting two futures at once.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Yet both men looked at her as though she belonged&#xD;&#xA;to a version of herself she had not yet chosen.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;The city shimmered.&#xD;&#xA;Alive. Watching.&#xD;&#xA;Waiting.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Not all choices end in escape.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-4/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-6/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Scene VI — The Witness</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-6/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti-lotus/scene-6/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;excerpt-scene&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;The Witness&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p class=&#34;scene-subtitle&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Some things are not seen—they are remembered.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;The painting had not changed.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Elsa had.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Each time she returned, the figure in the frame&#xD;&#xA;felt closer to recognition—&#xD;&#xA;as though it had always known her.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;And now, it was waiting to be acknowledged.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;scene-navigation&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-5/&#34;&gt;← Previous&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/excerpts/shakti/scene-1/&#34;&gt;Next →&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
